4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT ESTABLISHING A GRANT PROGRAM TO INCREASE
5 COMMUNITY SHELTER CAPACITY TO SERVE THE HOMELESS POPULATION; ESTABLISHING CRITERIA
6 FOR GRANT AWARDS; PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AND
7 PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE AND A TERMINATION DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. State matching grants for homeless shelter capacity -- rulemaking
12 authority. (1) As soon as possible after July 1, 2025, from funds appropriated by the legislature for the
13 purposes of this section, the department of public health and human services shall grant eligible applicants
14 state matching funds to serve one or more of the following categories of persons:
15 (a) senior citizens;
16 (b) veterans;
17 (c) survivors of domestic violence;
18 (d) youth preparing to transition out of foster care due to age; or
19 (e) individuals with mental health needs or with a substance use disorder.
20 (2) An applicant for matching funds under this section:
21 (a) must be a local government or a nonprofit corporation meeting the requirements of Title 35,
22 chapter 2, that is exempt from taxation under section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code, 26 U.S.C.
23 501(c)(3);
24 (b) shall include in its grant application a detailed plan for how the applicant will collaborate with
25 existing homelessness service providers; and
26 (c) shall indicate the source and amount of matching funds for the project.
27 (3) In awarding grants, the department shall prioritize to the greatest extent possible projects that:
28 (a) provide for geographic diversity in funded projects;
