1 (b) address existing gaps in the ability of available shelter services to meet the community's need
2 for shelter services; and
3 (c) include the availability of local and federal matching funds.
4 (4) The department shall adopt rules to implement this section, including provisions for:
5 (a) the application process;
6 (b) criteria for grant awards; and
7 (c) information to be reported to the department by grant recipients.
8 (5) The department shall report to the children, families, health, and human services interim
9 committee no later than August 30, 2026, on the results of the grant program.
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Appropriation. There is appropriated $2 million from the general fund to
12 the department of public health and human services for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, for the purposes
13 of [section 1]. Funds that are unencumbered on June 30, 2027, must revert to the general fund.
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
16 integral part of Title 53, chapter 2, part 2, and the provisions of Title 53, chapter 2, part 2, apply to [section 1].
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Termination. [This act] terminates June 30, 2027.
